In article <931105.33606.SSCOGGINS@delphi.com> SSCOGGINS@delphi.com writes:

>Does anyone know a FTP site with the latest version of IRIS.
> 
>The following is the description of version 3.5
> 
> 
>                                       IRIS
>                                       ----
> 
>                          A Cryptographic Security System
> 
>                                   Version 3.5
> 
>                                   March  1989
> 
>    IRIS   implements  commercial  cryptographic  techniques  under   the   DOS
>    environment:
> 
>              RSA public key cryptography
> 
>              DES cryptography
> 
>              VERNAM (XOR) cryptography
> 
>              PLAYFAIR cryptography
> 
>              CRC (checksum) generation
> 
>              Secure file erasure
> 
>    IRIS  is  intended  to be used by users with a need to  store  or  exchange
>    sensitive information in a secure manner.


I'm not sure that there have been any further freeware releases. I tried to 
talk the developer into something a while back but without success.

Do note that the IRIS implementation  of RSA is limited to keys of 512 bits or 
less.

